content: Very nice app! If you could add a feature that alerts you when players join or leave that would be neat!
replyContent: Hi, thank you for your review! Due to Android battery restrictions this is pretty much impossible to do in (near) real-time on the device itself. That's why I've created an external service called RustBot which is (among other things) able to do this. You can check it out if you want.

content: Really awesome! Please add one more thing though and it would be perfect! Could the RustBot part add a trigger that announces a message to the broadcast global chat for when someone dies or another player kills another player? Like "John died to starvation" or "John killed by Jane"?
replyContent: Hi, if you want to broadcast different kinds of messages, you'll have to create two separate triggers which execute a "say" command. You can then use regular expressions (press the help button in the trigger screen for more info) to set the trigger to death messages in the console. Feel free to send me another email if you need more help :)
